  "items": [
    {
      "_id": "DyJh1dkYvahKfMB9",
      "name": "Flesh-Crushing Stride",
      "type": "feat",
      "system": {
        "source": {
          "custom": "",
          "book": "MPMM",
          "page": "152",
          "license": ""
        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The hellfire engine moves up to its speed in a straight line. During this move, it can enter Large or smaller creatures' spaces. A creature whose space the hellfire engine enters must make a [[/save ability=dexterity dc=18]] saving throw. On a successful save, the creature is pushed to the nearest space out of the hellfire engine's path. On a failed save, the creature falls &amp;Reference[condition=prone] and takes 28 ([[/damage 8d6 type=bludgeoning]]) damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If the hellfire engine remains in the &amp;Reference[condition=prone] creature's space, the creature is also &amp;Reference[condition=restrained] until it's no longer in the same space as the hellfire engine. While &amp;Reference[condition=restrained] in this way, the creature, or another creature within 5 feet of it, can make a [[/save ability=strength dc=18]] check. On a success, the creature is shunted to an unoccupied space of its choice within 5 feet of the hellfire engine and is no longer &amp;Reference[condition=restrained].</p></div>",
